Create Report Page 1 - Worst and Best Zip Codes

Now we need to create a report with visuals as seen in the picture below. We want to showcase the best and worst zip codes. The page is divided into a logo on top left corner and a top center title. We also have two slicers (1-2), one for years and one for type of crime. Then we have 3 charts showcasing the worst zip codes (3-5) followed by three charts showcasing the best zip codes (6-8).



Click on "Report" tab to access the visualisation part of Power BI.


1. Slicer  - Year:

    1. Add a slicer visualization

    2. choose Year as Field 


2. Slicer - Type of Crime:

            a) Add a slicer visualization and choose Primary Type


            b)  Change to list by clicking slicer ellipsis


3. Stacked Bar Chart - 10 Highest Zip Codes by Crime Count

    a) Click on the Stacked Bar Chart Visual

    b) Add Zip codes to Axis, Arrest as Legend and Case Number to Value. Make sure Case Number is aggregating on Count


    c) Add a Visual level filter.

        - Click on Zip Codes
        - Choose Filter Type "Top N"
        - Add "10" to filter top 10
        - Drag Case Number to By value. Make sure its aggregating on Count.
        - Click "Apply Filter"


    d) We want to edit the look of the chart to make it more appealing to the user. We can do this by accessing the Format tab for the visual. 


        We want to change the color for the data

Also, lets format and rename the title to "10 Highest Zip Codes by Crime Count" and change font, size and color



4. Map - Worst Zip Codes by Crime 

    a) Add Map visualization


    b) Under Fields choose the following:

        - Legend: Zip Codes

        - Latitude: Latitude

        - Longitude: Longitude

        - Size: Sum of ID


    c) You will notice that the map doesn't work and this is because the latitude and longitude values are being aggregated to an average.         Click the arrow and choose "Don't summarize "


    c) In Visual Level Filter: Add Top N = 5 on Zip codes to show only top 5 Zip Codes. 

        Go to filters and choose to filter on Zip Codes. Choose Top N and add the number 5. Add ID as value and change it to SUM of ID.


    d) Format the visual for better user experience. By editing the title text, font and color.



5. Stacked Bar Chart - Crime Change % 2001-2019 by Zip Codes

    a) Add a new Stacked Bar Chart


    b) Add Zip Codes to Axis and Add Crime Change % 2001-2019 to Value


    c)  Add a Visual level filter.

        - Click on Zip Codes
        - Choose Filter Type "Top N"
        - Add "10" to filter top 10
        - Drag Crime Change % 2001-2019
        - Click "Apply Filter"


    d) Format the visual for better user experience. By editing the title text, font and color.

    d) We also need to see the results in %. So mark Crime Change % 2001-2019 measure and click % sign under Format:Percentage



Now copy these 3 visuals and place these under the existing ones. But we will change the Filter TOP N to be bottom results and also change the titles to the following:

Visual 4: 10 Lowest Zip Codes by Crime Count

Visual 5: Best Zip Codes by Crime

Visual 6: Crime Change % 2001-2019 by Zip Codes

    a) Mark on of the top 3 visuals. Use ctrl+c to copy. Use ctrl+v to paste.

    b) Change the Filter to sort bottom values instead of top values.

    c) Change the title

    d) Repeat for the 2 other visuals for a completed report page:
